headline: Why Tesla (TSLA) Shares Are Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of electric vehicle pioneer Tesla (NASDAQ:TSLA) fell 3.8% in the morning session after investor concerns grew as one of the United States' largest pension funds, the California Public Employees' Retirement System (Calpers), stated it would vote against CEO Elon Musk's 2025 performance award.

headline: Altria (NYSE:MO) Reports Sales Below Analyst Estimates In Q3 Earnings, Stock Drops
summary: Tobacco company Altria (NYSE:MO) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales falling 1.7% year on year to $5.25 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.45 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
